{
  "video_id": "uUH5YI5dTOg",
  "method": "api",
  "language": null,
  "duration_seconds": 7.125232100000176,
  "entry_count": 283,
  "error": null,
  "entries": [
    {
      "time": "00:01",
      "start": 1.5,
      "end": 3.866,
      "duration": 2.366,
      "text": "- [Voiceover] So, let me\ngive you an analogy, here."
    },
    {
      "time": "00:03",
      "start": 3.866,
      "end": 6.833,
      "duration": 2.967,
      "text": "When you were still an\nadorable little baby,"
    },
    {
      "time": "00:06",
      "start": 6.833,
      "end": 9.434000000000001,
      "duration": 2.601,
      "text": "you were just bursting with potential."
    },
    {
      "time": "00:09",
      "start": 9.434,
      "end": 11.133,
      "duration": 1.699,
      "text": "You could decide to be a pilot,"
    },
    {
      "time": "00:11",
      "start": 11.133,
      "end": 13.533,
      "duration": 2.4,
      "text": "or a doctor, or a journalist."
    },
    {
      "time": "00:13",
      "start": 13.533,
      "end": 16.133,
      "duration": 2.6,
      "text": "You had the potential to specialize into"
    },
    {
      "time": "00:16",
      "start": 16.133,
      "end": 18.333,
      "duration": 2.2,
      "text": "all sorts of different careers,"
    },
    {
      "time": "00:18",
      "start": 18.333,
      "end": 20.933,
      "duration": 2.6,
      "text": "and as you got a bit older,\nyou got more and more"
    },
    {
      "time": "00:20",
      "start": 20.933,
      "end": 23.267,
      "duration": 2.334,
      "text": "committed down a certain pathway,"
    },
    {
      "time": "00:23",
      "start": 23.267,
      "end": 24.7,
      "duration": 1.433,
      "text": "and the decisions that you made"
    },
    {
      "time": "00:24",
      "start": 24.7,
      "end": 28.366,
      "duration": 3.666,
      "text": "moved you further and further\nalong this pathway, right?"
    },
    {
      "time": "00:28",
      "start": 28.366,
      "end": 32.4,
      "duration": 4.034,
      "text": "Well, it turns out that stem\ncells operate in a similar way,"
    },
    {
      "time": "00:32",
      "start": 32.4,
      "end": 35.138,
      "duration": 2.738,
      "text": "going from unspecialized\nto more specialized"
    },
    {
      "time": "00:35",
      "start": 35.138,
      "end": 36.666,
      "duration": 1.528,
      "text": "as they get older."
    },
    {
      "time": "00:36",
      "start": 36.666,
      "end": 38.266999999999996,
      "duration": 1.601,
      "text": "So, let me show you what I mean by that"
    },
    {
      "time": "00:38",
      "start": 38.267,
      "end": 40.033,
      "duration": 1.766,
      "text": "over the course of this video."
    },
    {
      "time": "00:40",
      "start": 40.033,
      "end": 42.370000000000005,
      "duration": 2.337,
      "text": "And let's actually start\nback at the zygote, here,"
    },
    {
      "time": "00:42",
      "start": 42.37,
      "end": 45.3,
      "duration": 2.93,
      "text": "the cell that results\nwhen sperm and egg fuse"
    },
    {
      "time": "00:45",
      "start": 45.3,
      "end": 46.8,
      "duration": 1.5,
      "text": "because that's really where our stem cell"
    },
    {
      "time": "00:46",
      "start": 46.8,
      "end": 49.199999999999996,
      "duration": 2.4,
      "text": "story kinda begins."
    },
    {
      "time": "00:49",
      "start": 49.2,
      "end": 51.5,
      "duration": 2.3,
      "text": "So, the zygote starts to divide, right,"
    },
    {
      "time": "00:51",
      "start": 51.5,
      "end": 55.833,
      "duration": 4.333,
      "text": "by mitosis until it reaches\nthe blastocyst stage,"
    },
    {
      "time": "00:55",
      "start": 55.833,
      "end": 59.565999999999995,
      "duration": 3.733,
      "text": "this hollow ball of cells\nhere is called a blastocyst."
    },
    {
      "time": "00:59",
      "start": 59.566,
      "end": 63.266000000000005,
      "duration": 3.7,
      "text": "And here, things start to get\na little bit more interesting."
    },
    {
      "time": "01:03",
      "start": 63.266,
      "end": 66.8,
      "duration": 3.534,
      "text": "So, in a blastocyst, there's\nthis little grouping of cells"
    },
    {
      "time": "01:06",
      "start": 66.8,
      "end": 70.336,
      "duration": 3.536,
      "text": "down in here, referred to\nas the inner cell mass."
    },
    {
      "time": "01:10",
      "start": 70.336,
      "end": 72.934,
      "duration": 2.598,
      "text": "And this is a really special\nlittle bunch of cells"
    },
    {
      "time": "01:12",
      "start": 72.934,
      "end": 75.53699999999999,
      "duration": 2.603,
      "text": "that go on to become the embryo."
    },
    {
      "time": "01:15",
      "start": 75.537,
      "end": 78.366,
      "duration": 2.829,
      "text": "So, these are called stem cells."
    },
    {
      "time": "01:18",
      "start": 78.366,
      "end": 80.2,
      "duration": 1.834,
      "text": "And what they can do as stem cells"
    },
    {
      "time": "01:20",
      "start": 80.2,
      "end": 84.10000000000001,
      "duration": 3.9,
      "text": "is they can specialize into\nseveral other cell types."
    },
    {
      "time": "01:24",
      "start": 84.1,
      "end": 87.43299999999999,
      "duration": 3.333,
      "text": "So, we actually call them\npluripotent stem cells."
    },
    {
      "time": "01:27",
      "start": 87.433,
      "end": 89.86600000000001,
      "duration": 2.433,
      "text": "Pluri meaning several and potent referring"
    },
    {
      "time": "01:29",
      "start": 89.866,
      "end": 91.9,
      "duration": 2.034,
      "text": "to these stem cells' ability to actually"
    },
    {
      "time": "01:31",
      "start": 91.9,
      "end": 94.433,
      "duration": 2.533,
      "text": "do this differentiation."
    },
    {
      "time": "01:34",
      "start": 94.433,
      "end": 97.033,
      "duration": 2.6,
      "text": "So, during development,\nthese inner cell mass"
    },
    {
      "time": "01:37",
      "start": 97.033,
      "end": 99.8,
      "duration": 2.767,
      "text": "pluripotent stem cells can differentiate"
    },
    {
      "time": "01:39",
      "start": 99.8,
      "end": 103.03399999999999,
      "duration": 3.234,
      "text": "into any of the more than\n200 different cell types"
    },
    {
      "time": "01:43",
      "start": 103.034,
      "end": 107.10000000000001,
      "duration": 4.066,
      "text": "in the adult human body when\ngiven the proper stimulation."
    },
    {
      "time": "01:47",
      "start": 107.1,
      "end": 109.134,
      "duration": 2.034,
      "text": "So, it's kind of incredible to think"
    },
    {
      "time": "01:49",
      "start": 109.134,
      "end": 111.333,
      "duration": 2.199,
      "text": "that every single cell in your body"
    },
    {
      "time": "01:51",
      "start": 111.333,
      "end": 113.3,
      "duration": 1.967,
      "text": "can trace its ancestry back to this"
    },
    {
      "time": "01:53",
      "start": 113.3,
      "end": 115.26599999999999,
      "duration": 1.966,
      "text": "little group of stem cells, here."
    },
    {
      "time": "01:55",
      "start": 115.266,
      "end": 116.80000000000001,
      "duration": 1.534,
      "text": "And actually, if you ever hear anyone"
    },
    {
      "time": "01:56",
      "start": 116.8,
      "end": 118.866,
      "duration": 2.066,
      "text": "talking about embryonic stem cells,"
    },
    {
      "time": "01:58",
      "start": 118.866,
      "end": 120.566,
      "duration": 1.7,
      "text": "these are the ones they're referring to,"
    },
    {
      "time": "02:00",
      "start": 120.566,
      "end": 123.233,
      "duration": 2.667,
      "text": "these ICM stem cells."
    },
    {
      "time": "02:03",
      "start": 123.233,
      "end": 125.733,
      "duration": 2.5,
      "text": "So, is this the only place\nwe can find stem cells,"
    },
    {
      "time": "02:05",
      "start": 125.733,
      "end": 128.53300000000002,
      "duration": 2.8,
      "text": "here in the developmental structures?"
    },
    {
      "time": "02:08",
      "start": 128.533,
      "end": 130.5,
      "duration": 1.967,
      "text": "We used to think so, but, it turns out"
    },
    {
      "time": "02:10",
      "start": 130.5,
      "end": 133.833,
      "duration": 3.333,
      "text": "that in mammals, there are\ntwo main types of stem cells."
    },
    {
      "time": "02:13",
      "start": 133.833,
      "end": 135.96699999999998,
      "duration": 2.134,
      "text": "Embryonic stem cells that we just saw"
    },
    {
      "time": "02:15",
      "start": 135.967,
      "end": 139.466,
      "duration": 3.499,
      "text": "and somatic stem cells which\nare found in every person."
    },
    {
      "time": "02:19",
      "start": 139.466,
      "end": 142.77100000000002,
      "duration": 3.305,
      "text": "So, the embryonic stem cells\nare used to build our bodies,"
    },
    {
      "time": "02:22",
      "start": 142.771,
      "end": 146.56699999999998,
      "duration": 3.796,
      "text": "to go from one cell to\ntrillions of specialized cells,"
    },
    {
      "time": "02:26",
      "start": 146.567,
      "end": 148.26600000000002,
      "duration": 1.699,
      "text": "and the somatic stem cells are used"
    },
    {
      "time": "02:28",
      "start": 148.266,
      "end": 150.89999999999998,
      "duration": 2.634,
      "text": "as sort of a repair system for the body,"
    },
    {
      "time": "02:30",
      "start": 150.9,
      "end": 153.833,
      "duration": 2.933,
      "text": "replenishing tissues\nthat need to be replaced."
    },
    {
      "time": "02:33",
      "start": 153.833,
      "end": 155.7,
      "duration": 1.867,
      "text": "And they can't repair everything,"
    },
    {
      "time": "02:35",
      "start": 155.7,
      "end": 157.533,
      "duration": 1.833,
      "text": "but, there's a lot of every day repairs"
    },
    {
      "time": "02:37",
      "start": 157.533,
      "end": 160.2,
      "duration": 2.667,
      "text": "that can happen because of our stem cells."
    },
    {
      "time": "02:40",
      "start": 160.2,
      "end": 162.36599999999999,
      "duration": 2.166,
      "text": "So, in skin, for example..."
    },
    {
      "time": "02:44",
      "start": 164.3,
      "end": 167.43300000000002,
      "duration": 3.133,
      "text": "This outside layer is the part\nof our skin that we can see"
    },
    {
      "time": "02:47",
      "start": 167.433,
      "end": 169.266,
      "duration": 1.833,
      "text": "and that we can touch, right?"
    },
    {
      "time": "02:49",
      "start": 169.266,
      "end": 171.36599999999999,
      "duration": 2.1,
      "text": "And it's made of these waterproof,"
    },
    {
      "time": "02:51",
      "start": 171.366,
      "end": 174.93300000000002,
      "duration": 3.567,
      "text": "pretty rugged epithelialor skin cells"
    },
    {
      "time": "02:54",
      "start": 174.933,
      "end": 178.066,
      "duration": 3.133,
      "text": "and interestingly, although\nthey are pretty rugged,"
    },
    {
      "time": "02:58",
      "start": 178.066,
      "end": 180.633,
      "duration": 2.567,
      "text": "you're constantly\nshedding these skin cells."
    },
    {
      "time": "03:00",
      "start": 180.633,
      "end": 183.43300000000002,
      "duration": 2.8,
      "text": "They actually just sort of\nfall off or get rubbed off"
    },
    {
      "time": "03:03",
      "start": 183.433,
      "end": 184.79999999999998,
      "duration": 1.367,
      "text": "during every day activities like"
    },
    {
      "time": "03:04",
      "start": 184.8,
      "end": 186.86700000000002,
      "duration": 2.067,
      "text": "when you're putting your clothes on."
    },
    {
      "time": "03:06",
      "start": 186.867,
      "end": 188.233,
      "duration": 1.366,
      "text": "And then, the ones from underneath them"
    },
    {
      "time": "03:08",
      "start": 188.233,
      "end": 190.70000000000002,
      "duration": 2.467,
      "text": "just sort of move up and take their place."
    },
    {
      "time": "03:10",
      "start": 190.7,
      "end": 192.033,
      "duration": 1.333,
      "text": "So, you shed them and you lose"
    },
    {
      "time": "03:12",
      "start": 192.033,
      "end": 195.29999999999998,
      "duration": 3.267,
      "text": "almost 40,000 of them per hour."
    },
    {
      "time": "03:15",
      "start": 195.3,
      "end": 198.246,
      "duration": 2.946,
      "text": "So, if we wanna have any\nhope of keeping our skin,"
    },
    {
      "time": "03:18",
      "start": 198.246,
      "end": 200.566,
      "duration": 2.32,
      "text": "we kinda need a way to\nreplace these cells,"
    },
    {
      "time": "03:20",
      "start": 200.566,
      "end": 202.167,
      "duration": 1.601,
      "text": "and that's where stem cells that live"
    },
    {
      "time": "03:22",
      "start": 202.167,
      "end": 203.8,
      "duration": 1.633,
      "text": "in our skin come in."
    },
    {
      "time": "03:23",
      "start": 203.8,
      "end": 205.133,
      "duration": 1.333,
      "text": "Actually, our skin cells are shed"
    },
    {
      "time": "03:25",
      "start": 205.133,
      "end": 208.3,
      "duration": 3.167,
      "text": "and replaced so often,\nthat it only takes a month"
    },
    {
      "time": "03:28",
      "start": 208.3,
      "end": 211.733,
      "duration": 3.433,
      "text": "for us to have a completely new skin."
    },
    {
      "time": "03:31",
      "start": 211.733,
      "end": 215.034,
      "duration": 3.301,
      "text": "Like, literally one\nmonth, entirely new skin."
    },
    {
      "time": "03:35",
      "start": 215.034,
      "end": 216.63299999999998,
      "duration": 1.599,
      "text": "It's outrageous."
    },
    {
      "time": "03:36",
      "start": 216.633,
      "end": 219.233,
      "duration": 2.6,
      "text": "Anyway, deep within our skin,"
    },
    {
      "time": "03:39",
      "start": 219.233,
      "end": 220.667,
      "duration": 1.434,
      "text": "there's this layer of stem cells"
    },
    {
      "time": "03:40",
      "start": 220.667,
      "end": 223.166,
      "duration": 2.499,
      "text": "called epidermal stem cells,"
    },
    {
      "time": "03:43",
      "start": 223.166,
      "end": 225.966,
      "duration": 2.8,
      "text": "and their job is to be\ncontinually dividing."
    },
    {
      "time": "03:45",
      "start": 225.966,
      "end": 227.966,
      "duration": 2.0,
      "text": "So, you can see them\ndividing, here, dividing,"
    },
    {
      "time": "03:47",
      "start": 227.966,
      "end": 231.267,
      "duration": 3.301,
      "text": "dividing, dividing, and making\nnew skin cells that go on"
    },
    {
      "time": "03:51",
      "start": 231.267,
      "end": 235.267,
      "duration": 4.0,
      "text": "to migrate upward as the\nmultiple layers of our skin."
    },
    {
      "time": "03:55",
      "start": 235.267,
      "end": 237.133,
      "duration": 1.866,
      "text": "And their goal is to eventually replace"
    },
    {
      "time": "03:57",
      "start": 237.133,
      "end": 238.9,
      "duration": 1.767,
      "text": "these ones up here on the outside"
    },
    {
      "time": "03:58",
      "start": 238.9,
      "end": 241.76600000000002,
      "duration": 2.866,
      "text": "that get damaged or worn out and fall off."
    },
    {
      "time": "04:01",
      "start": 241.766,
      "end": 243.36599999999999,
      "duration": 1.6,
      "text": "So, it's this kind of activity here"
    },
    {
      "time": "04:03",
      "start": 243.366,
      "end": 245.76700000000002,
      "duration": 2.401,
      "text": "which show off our stem cells' role"
    },
    {
      "time": "04:05",
      "start": 245.767,
      "end": 247.833,
      "duration": 2.066,
      "text": "as our regenerative cells."
    },
    {
      "time": "04:07",
      "start": 247.833,
      "end": 249.4,
      "duration": 1.567,
      "text": "Now, lemme just highlight\na few differences"
    },
    {
      "time": "04:09",
      "start": 249.4,
      "end": 252.167,
      "duration": 2.767,
      "text": "between our mature skin cells over here"
    },
    {
      "time": "04:12",
      "start": 252.167,
      "end": 254.133,
      "duration": 1.966,
      "text": "and our stem cells down here."
    },
    {
      "time": "04:14",
      "start": 254.133,
      "end": 256.13300000000004,
      "duration": 2.0,
      "text": "They are very different."
    },
    {
      "time": "04:16",
      "start": 256.133,
      "end": 258.53299999999996,
      "duration": 2.4,
      "text": "Mature cells are not\nthe same as stem cells,"
    },
    {
      "time": "04:18",
      "start": 258.533,
      "end": 261.0,
      "duration": 2.467,
      "text": "and this principle goes\nfor really any mature cell"
    },
    {
      "time": "04:21",
      "start": 261.0,
      "end": 263.034,
      "duration": 2.034,
      "text": "versus any stem cell."
    },
    {
      "time": "04:23",
      "start": 263.034,
      "end": 265.667,
      "duration": 2.633,
      "text": "So, the mature cell is\nalready specialized,"
    },
    {
      "time": "04:25",
      "start": 265.667,
      "end": 268.73299999999995,
      "duration": 3.066,
      "text": "it already has a really specific function."
    },
    {
      "time": "04:28",
      "start": 268.733,
      "end": 272.033,
      "duration": 3.3,
      "text": "For example, our outer layer\nof epithelial cells, here,"
    },
    {
      "time": "04:32",
      "start": 272.033,
      "end": 273.433,
      "duration": 1.4,
      "text": "they have a protective function"
    },
    {
      "time": "04:33",
      "start": 273.433,
      "end": 275.566,
      "duration": 2.133,
      "text": "against the outside environment."
    },
    {
      "time": "04:35",
      "start": 275.566,
      "end": 278.0,
      "duration": 2.434,
      "text": "And, you know, just thinking\nof other adult cell types,"
    },
    {
      "time": "04:38",
      "start": 278.0,
      "end": 281.033,
      "duration": 3.033,
      "text": "right, like muscle cells\nhave a contractile function,"
    },
    {
      "time": "04:41",
      "start": 281.033,
      "end": 283.433,
      "duration": 2.4,
      "text": "and neurons have a\nmessage sending function,"
    },
    {
      "time": "04:43",
      "start": 283.433,
      "end": 286.633,
      "duration": 3.2,
      "text": "and bones have a rigid\nstructural function."
    },
    {
      "time": "04:46",
      "start": 286.633,
      "end": 288.79999999999995,
      "duration": 2.167,
      "text": "So, all these adult cells are already nice"
    },
    {
      "time": "04:48",
      "start": 288.8,
      "end": 291.10200000000003,
      "duration": 2.302,
      "text": "and specialized, they've\ngrown up and decided"
    },
    {
      "time": "04:51",
      "start": 291.102,
      "end": 293.0,
      "duration": 1.898,
      "text": "what they wanna do for a living,"
    },
    {
      "time": "04:53",
      "start": 293.0,
      "end": 295.2,
      "duration": 2.2,
      "text": "whereas, stem cells are\nnot like that at all."
    },
    {
      "time": "04:55",
      "start": 295.2,
      "end": 297.334,
      "duration": 2.134,
      "text": "Stem cells are unspecialized."
    },
    {
      "time": "04:57",
      "start": 297.334,
      "end": 299.66700000000003,
      "duration": 2.333,
      "text": "But, they still have a\nreally important job,"
    },
    {
      "time": "04:59",
      "start": 299.667,
      "end": 303.26599999999996,
      "duration": 3.599,
      "text": "which is to give rise to our\nmore specialized cell types,"
    },
    {
      "time": "05:03",
      "start": 303.266,
      "end": 305.86600000000004,
      "duration": 2.6,
      "text": "like these cells here, okay?"
    },
    {
      "time": "05:05",
      "start": 305.866,
      "end": 309.26599999999996,
      "duration": 3.4,
      "text": "And, actually, in order to\nbe considered a stem cell,"
    },
    {
      "time": "05:09",
      "start": 309.266,
      "end": 311.73400000000004,
      "duration": 2.468,
      "text": "and this goes for the\nembryonic stem cells we met"
    },
    {
      "time": "05:11",
      "start": 311.734,
      "end": 315.20099999999996,
      "duration": 3.467,
      "text": "previously and the somatic\nstem cells we're meeting now,"
    },
    {
      "time": "05:15",
      "start": 315.201,
      "end": 317.06600000000003,
      "duration": 1.865,
      "text": "to be a stem cell, you'd need to possess"
    },
    {
      "time": "05:17",
      "start": 317.066,
      "end": 319.26599999999996,
      "duration": 2.2,
      "text": "two main properties."
    },
    {
      "time": "05:19",
      "start": 319.266,
      "end": 322.8,
      "duration": 3.534,
      "text": "The ability to self renew,\nmeaning you can divide"
    },
    {
      "time": "05:22",
      "start": 322.8,
      "end": 324.7,
      "duration": 1.9,
      "text": "and divide, and divide, but, at least"
    },
    {
      "time": "05:24",
      "start": 324.7,
      "end": 328.43399999999997,
      "duration": 3.734,
      "text": "one of your resulting\ncells remains a stem cell,"
    },
    {
      "time": "05:28",
      "start": 328.434,
      "end": 330.66700000000003,
      "duration": 2.233,
      "text": "it remains undifferentiated,"
    },
    {
      "time": "05:30",
      "start": 330.667,
      "end": 333.23299999999995,
      "duration": 2.566,
      "text": "and you'd need to have a high capacity"
    },
    {
      "time": "05:33",
      "start": 333.233,
      "end": 335.56600000000003,
      "duration": 2.333,
      "text": "to differentiate into\nmore specialized cells"
    },
    {
      "time": "05:35",
      "start": 335.566,
      "end": 337.167,
      "duration": 1.601,
      "text": "when the time comes."
    },
    {
      "time": "05:37",
      "start": 337.167,
      "end": 338.76599999999996,
      "duration": 1.599,
      "text": "So, remember, this is also referred to"
    },
    {
      "time": "05:38",
      "start": 338.766,
      "end": 341.233,
      "duration": 2.467,
      "text": "as having some degree of potency."
    },
    {
      "time": "05:41",
      "start": 341.233,
      "end": 342.833,
      "duration": 1.6,
      "text": "And there's actually a few different types"
    },
    {
      "time": "05:42",
      "start": 342.833,
      "end": 345.01500000000004,
      "duration": 2.182,
      "text": "of stem cells, and some\nof them can turn into"
    },
    {
      "time": "05:45",
      "start": 345.015,
      "end": 346.9,
      "duration": 1.885,
      "text": "more types of cells than others."
    },
    {
      "time": "05:46",
      "start": 346.9,
      "end": 349.00199999999995,
      "duration": 2.102,
      "text": "Some are more potent than others."
    },
    {
      "time": "05:49",
      "start": 349.002,
      "end": 351.3,
      "duration": 2.298,
      "text": "So, this epithelial stem cell we saw here"
    },
    {
      "time": "05:51",
      "start": 351.3,
      "end": 354.06600000000003,
      "duration": 2.766,
      "text": "is actually one of the less\npotent types of stem cell."
    },
    {
      "time": "05:54",
      "start": 354.066,
      "end": 356.666,
      "duration": 2.6,
      "text": "In other words, these\nstem cells can only divide"
    },
    {
      "time": "05:56",
      "start": 356.666,
      "end": 360.4,
      "duration": 3.734,
      "text": "and specialize into more epithelial cells."
    },
    {
      "time": "06:00",
      "start": 360.4,
      "end": 363.33299999999997,
      "duration": 2.933,
      "text": "So, they're our source of\nepithelial cells, sure,"
    },
    {
      "time": "06:03",
      "start": 363.333,
      "end": 367.067,
      "duration": 3.734,
      "text": "but, only epithelial cells\nand not any other cell type."
    },
    {
      "time": "06:07",
      "start": 367.067,
      "end": 369.6,
      "duration": 2.533,
      "text": "So, we call them unipotent,\nreferring to their"
    },
    {
      "time": "06:09",
      "start": 369.6,
      "end": 373.13300000000004,
      "duration": 3.533,
      "text": "ability to only create one type of cell."
    },
    {
      "time": "06:13",
      "start": 373.133,
      "end": 375.0,
      "duration": 1.867,
      "text": "But, lemme show you another example here"
    },
    {
      "time": "06:15",
      "start": 375.0,
      "end": 378.2,
      "duration": 3.2,
      "text": "of a multipotent stem cell."
    },
    {
      "time": "06:18",
      "start": 378.2,
      "end": 380.86699999999996,
      "duration": 2.667,
      "text": "Let's look at this guy's\nfemur, his thigh bone,"
    },
    {
      "time": "06:20",
      "start": 380.867,
      "end": 382.433,
      "duration": 1.566,
      "text": "which is where our blood cells are made"
    },
    {
      "time": "06:22",
      "start": 382.433,
      "end": 385.266,
      "duration": 2.833,
      "text": "inside bone marrow in our bones."
    },
    {
      "time": "06:25",
      "start": 385.266,
      "end": 387.20000000000005,
      "duration": 1.934,
      "text": "So, you might know that\nour red blood cells"
    },
    {
      "time": "06:27",
      "start": 387.2,
      "end": 389.666,
      "duration": 2.466,
      "text": "have a life span of about four months."
    },
    {
      "time": "06:29",
      "start": 389.666,
      "end": 392.233,
      "duration": 2.567,
      "text": "So, that means that we need\nto be constantly replacing"
    },
    {
      "time": "06:32",
      "start": 392.233,
      "end": 395.1,
      "duration": 2.867,
      "text": "our red blood cells or\nwe'll run out, right?"
    },
    {
      "time": "06:35",
      "start": 395.1,
      "end": 397.533,
      "duration": 2.433,
      "text": "Well, in our bone marrow,\nwe have what are called"
    },
    {
      "time": "06:37",
      "start": 397.533,
      "end": 400.3,
      "duration": 2.767,
      "text": "hematopoietic stem cells, which are our"
    },
    {
      "time": "06:40",
      "start": 400.3,
      "end": 402.599,
      "duration": 2.299,
      "text": "blood making stem cells."
    },
    {
      "time": "06:42",
      "start": 402.599,
      "end": 404.19599999999997,
      "duration": 1.597,
      "text": "And these are pretty special,"
    },
    {
      "time": "06:44",
      "start": 404.196,
      "end": 406.033,
      "duration": 1.837,
      "text": "they're multipotent stem cells,"
    },
    {
      "time": "06:46",
      "start": 406.033,
      "end": 408.966,
      "duration": 2.933,
      "text": "which means they can give\nrise to many types of cells,"
    },
    {
      "time": "06:48",
      "start": 408.966,
      "end": 412.16700000000003,
      "duration": 3.201,
      "text": "but, only ones within a specific family."
    },
    {
      "time": "06:52",
      "start": 412.167,
      "end": 415.43399999999997,
      "duration": 3.267,
      "text": "In this case, blood cells,\nand not, for example,"
    },
    {
      "time": "06:55",
      "start": 415.434,
      "end": 418.70000000000005,
      "duration": 3.266,
      "text": "cells of the nervous system\nor the skeletal system."
    },
    {
      "time": "06:58",
      "start": 418.7,
      "end": 420.366,
      "duration": 1.666,
      "text": "So, our hematopoietic stem cells"
    },
    {
      "time": "07:00",
      "start": 420.366,
      "end": 423.03299999999996,
      "duration": 2.667,
      "text": "are always busy churning\nout new blood cells,"
    },
    {
      "time": "07:03",
      "start": 423.033,
      "end": 425.233,
      "duration": 2.2,
      "text": "red blood cells to carry oxygen for us,"
    },
    {
      "time": "07:05",
      "start": 425.233,
      "end": 426.633,
      "duration": 1.4,
      "text": "and white blood cells to keep"
    },
    {
      "time": "07:06",
      "start": 426.633,
      "end": 429.86699999999996,
      "duration": 3.234,
      "text": "our immune system nice and strong."
    },
    {
      "time": "07:09",
      "start": 429.867,
      "end": 432.067,
      "duration": 2.2,
      "text": "And for a more clinical example,"
    },
    {
      "time": "07:12",
      "start": 432.067,
      "end": 434.466,
      "duration": 2.399,
      "text": "with blood diseases like leukemia,"
    },
    {
      "time": "07:14",
      "start": 434.466,
      "end": 436.90000000000003,
      "duration": 2.434,
      "text": "certain blood cells\nwill grow uncontrollably"
    },
    {
      "time": "07:16",
      "start": 436.9,
      "end": 438.46599999999995,
      "duration": 1.566,
      "text": "within a patient's bone marrow,"
    },
    {
      "time": "07:18",
      "start": 438.466,
      "end": 440.5,
      "duration": 2.034,
      "text": "and it actually crowds out their healthy"
    },
    {
      "time": "07:20",
      "start": 440.5,
      "end": 442.133,
      "duration": 1.633,
      "text": "stem cells, here, from being able"
    },
    {
      "time": "07:22",
      "start": 442.133,
      "end": 444.166,
      "duration": 2.033,
      "text": "to produce enough blood cells."
    },
    {
      "time": "07:24",
      "start": 444.166,
      "end": 446.666,
      "duration": 2.5,
      "text": "So, as part of treatment,\nonce the leukemia cells"
    },
    {
      "time": "07:26",
      "start": 446.666,
      "end": 449.866,
      "duration": 3.2,
      "text": "are cleared from the bone marrow\nwith, usually, chemotherapy"
    },
    {
      "time": "07:29",
      "start": 449.866,
      "end": 451.866,
      "duration": 2.0,
      "text": "or radiation, doctors can actually put"
    },
    {
      "time": "07:31",
      "start": 451.866,
      "end": 455.4,
      "duration": 3.534,
      "text": "more hematopoietic stem cells\nback into the bone marrow"
    },
    {
      "time": "07:35",
      "start": 455.4,
      "end": 457.435,
      "duration": 2.035,
      "text": "that then go on to produce normal amounts"
    },
    {
      "time": "07:37",
      "start": 457.435,
      "end": 459.033,
      "duration": 1.598,
      "text": "of blood for the person again."
    },
    {
      "time": "07:39",
      "start": 459.033,
      "end": 460.86600000000004,
      "duration": 1.833,
      "text": "So, this is probably the most common use"
    },
    {
      "time": "07:40",
      "start": 460.866,
      "end": 463.066,
      "duration": 2.2,
      "text": "of stem cells in medicine as of now."
    },
    {
      "time": "07:43",
      "start": 463.066,
      "end": 465.566,
      "duration": 2.5,
      "text": "And you can actually find\nthese multipotent stem cells"
    },
    {
      "time": "07:45",
      "start": 465.566,
      "end": 467.4,
      "duration": 1.834,
      "text": "in most tissues and organs."
    },
    {
      "time": "07:47",
      "start": 467.4,
      "end": 470.70099999999996,
      "duration": 3.301,
      "text": "So, for example, we have\nmultipotent neural stem cells"
    },
    {
      "time": "07:50",
      "start": 470.701,
      "end": 472.8,
      "duration": 2.099,
      "text": "that slowly give rise to neurons"
    },
    {
      "time": "07:52",
      "start": 472.8,
      "end": 475.3,
      "duration": 2.5,
      "text": "and their supporting cells when necessary."
    },
    {
      "time": "07:55",
      "start": 475.3,
      "end": 478.233,
      "duration": 2.933,
      "text": "And we have multipotent\nmesenchymal stem cells"
    },
    {
      "time": "07:58",
      "start": 478.233,
      "end": 479.933,
      "duration": 1.7,
      "text": "in a few different places in the body"
    },
    {
      "time": "07:59",
      "start": 479.933,
      "end": 483.09999999999997,
      "duration": 3.167,
      "text": "that give rise to bone\ncells and cartilage cells,"
    },
    {
      "time": "08:03",
      "start": 483.1,
      "end": 486.233,
      "duration": 3.133,
      "text": "and adipose cells."
    },
    {
      "time": "08:06",
      "start": 486.233,
      "end": 488.701,
      "duration": 2.468,
      "text": "So, you might be wondering\nafter seeing our epithelial"
    },
    {
      "time": "08:08",
      "start": 488.701,
      "end": 491.3,
      "duration": 2.599,
      "text": "and our hematopoietic stem cells dividing,"
    },
    {
      "time": "08:11",
      "start": 491.3,
      "end": 494.56600000000003,
      "duration": 3.266,
      "text": "why aren't these cells being\nused up as they divide?"
    },
    {
      "time": "08:14",
      "start": 494.566,
      "end": 496.433,
      "duration": 1.867,
      "text": "And that's a really good question."
    },
    {
      "time": "08:16",
      "start": 496.433,
      "end": 498.83299999999997,
      "duration": 2.4,
      "text": "So, stem cells have\ntwo mechanisms in place"
    },
    {
      "time": "08:18",
      "start": 498.833,
      "end": 502.06600000000003,
      "duration": 3.233,
      "text": "to make sure that their\nnumbers are maintained."
    },
    {
      "time": "08:22",
      "start": 502.066,
      "end": 504.53299999999996,
      "duration": 2.467,
      "text": "So, their first trick is\nthat when they divide,"
    },
    {
      "time": "08:24",
      "start": 504.533,
      "end": 508.966,
      "duration": 4.433,
      "text": "they undergo what's called\nobligate asymmetric replication"
    },
    {
      "time": "08:28",
      "start": 508.966,
      "end": 512.433,
      "duration": 3.467,
      "text": "where the stem cell divides\ninto one so called mother cell"
    },
    {
      "time": "08:32",
      "start": 512.433,
      "end": 515.4,
      "duration": 2.967,
      "text": "identical to the original stem cell,"
    },
    {
      "time": "08:35",
      "start": 515.4,
      "end": 518.1999999999999,
      "duration": 2.8,
      "text": "and one daughter cell\nthat's differentiated."
    },
    {
      "time": "08:38",
      "start": 518.2,
      "end": 520.033,
      "duration": 1.833,
      "text": "So, then, the daughter\ncell can go on to become"
    },
    {
      "time": "08:40",
      "start": 520.033,
      "end": 523.1,
      "duration": 3.067,
      "text": "more specialized while the mother cell"
    },
    {
      "time": "08:43",
      "start": 523.1,
      "end": 526.833,
      "duration": 3.733,
      "text": "replaces the stem cell\nthat divided, initially."
    },
    {
      "time": "08:46",
      "start": 526.833,
      "end": 531.1999999999999,
      "duration": 4.367,
      "text": "The other mechanism is called\nstochastic differentiation."
    },
    {
      "time": "08:51",
      "start": 531.2,
      "end": 534.2330000000001,
      "duration": 3.033,
      "text": "So, if one stem cell\nhappens to differentiate"
    },
    {
      "time": "08:54",
      "start": 534.233,
      "end": 537.9,
      "duration": 3.667,
      "text": "into two daughter cells instead\nof a mother and a daughter,"
    },
    {
      "time": "08:57",
      "start": 537.9,
      "end": 540.3,
      "duration": 2.4,
      "text": "another stem cell will notice this"
    },
    {
      "time": "09:00",
      "start": 540.3,
      "end": 542.9,
      "duration": 2.6,
      "text": "and makes up for the loss\nof the original stem cell"
    },
    {
      "time": "09:02",
      "start": 542.9,
      "end": 546.6999999999999,
      "duration": 3.8,
      "text": "by undergoing mitosis and\nproducing two stem cells"
    },
    {
      "time": "09:06",
      "start": 546.7,
      "end": 549.2,
      "duration": 2.5,
      "text": "identical to the original."
    },
    {
      "time": "09:09",
      "start": 549.2,
      "end": 550.7,
      "duration": 1.5,
      "text": "So, these two mechanisms make sure"
    },
    {
      "time": "09:10",
      "start": 550.7,
      "end": 553.3660000000001,
      "duration": 2.666,
      "text": "their numbers remain nice and strong."
    },
    {
      "time": "09:13",
      "start": 553.366,
      "end": 555.8,
      "duration": 2.434,
      "text": "So, we've looked at embryonic stem cells"
    },
    {
      "time": "09:15",
      "start": 555.8,
      "end": 558.3,
      "duration": 2.5,
      "text": "and we've looked at somatic stem cells."
    },
    {
      "time": "09:18",
      "start": 558.3,
      "end": 559.733,
      "duration": 1.433,
      "text": "There's actually one more type called"
    },
    {
      "time": "09:19",
      "start": 559.733,
      "end": 563.9659999999999,
      "duration": 4.233,
      "text": "induced pluripotent stem\ncells, or IPS cells."
    },
    {
      "time": "09:23",
      "start": 563.966,
      "end": 565.833,
      "duration": 1.867,
      "text": "It turns out that you\ncan actually introduce"
    },
    {
      "time": "09:25",
      "start": 565.833,
      "end": 570.8,
      "duration": 4.967,
      "text": "a few specific genes into\nalready specialized somatic cells"
    },
    {
      "time": "09:30",
      "start": 570.8,
      "end": 573.1999999999999,
      "duration": 2.4,
      "text": "like muscle cells, and\nthey'll sort of forget"
    },
    {
      "time": "09:33",
      "start": 573.2,
      "end": 575.933,
      "duration": 2.733,
      "text": "what type of cell they are,\nand they'll revert back,"
    },
    {
      "time": "09:35",
      "start": 575.933,
      "end": 579.333,
      "duration": 3.4,
      "text": "they'll be reprogrammed\ninto a pluripotent stem cell"
    },
    {
      "time": "09:39",
      "start": 579.333,
      "end": 581.6329999999999,
      "duration": 2.3,
      "text": "just like an embryonic stem cell."
    },
    {
      "time": "09:41",
      "start": 581.633,
      "end": 583.6,
      "duration": 1.967,
      "text": "And this is a huge discovery."
    },
    {
      "time": "09:43",
      "start": 583.6,
      "end": 585.8670000000001,
      "duration": 2.267,
      "text": "I mean, the technique is\nstill being perfected,"
    },
    {
      "time": "09:45",
      "start": 585.867,
      "end": 588.8,
      "duration": 2.933,
      "text": "but, there's a lot of\nmedicinal implications, here."
    },
    {
      "time": "09:48",
      "start": 588.8,
      "end": 591.966,
      "duration": 3.166,
      "text": "For example, IPS cells\nare basically the core"
    },
    {
      "time": "09:51",
      "start": 591.966,
      "end": 594.7,
      "duration": 2.734,
      "text": "of regenerative medicine,\nwhich is a pretty new field"
    },
    {
      "time": "09:54",
      "start": 594.7,
      "end": 597.7,
      "duration": 3.0,
      "text": "of medicine where the goal\nis to repair damaged tissues"
    },
    {
      "time": "09:57",
      "start": 597.7,
      "end": 600.1,
      "duration": 2.4,
      "text": "in a given person by using stem cells"
    },
    {
      "time": "10:00",
      "start": 600.1,
      "end": 601.868,
      "duration": 1.768,
      "text": "from their own body."
    },
    {
      "time": "10:01",
      "start": 601.868,
      "end": 604.633,
      "duration": 2.765,
      "text": "So, with IPS cells, each patient can have"
    },
    {
      "time": "10:04",
      "start": 604.633,
      "end": 607.134,
      "duration": 2.501,
      "text": "their own pluripotent stem cell line"
    },
    {
      "time": "10:07",
      "start": 607.134,
      "end": 609.966,
      "duration": 2.832,
      "text": "to theoretically replace\nany damaged organs"
    },
    {
      "time": "10:09",
      "start": 609.966,
      "end": 612.969,
      "duration": 3.003,
      "text": "with new ones made out of their own cells."
    },
    {
      "time": "10:12",
      "start": 612.969,
      "end": 615.2,
      "duration": 2.231,
      "text": "So, not only would a\npatient get the new organ"
    },
    {
      "time": "10:15",
      "start": 615.2,
      "end": 617.466,
      "duration": 2.266,
      "text": "they might need, but, there also won't be"
    },
    {
      "time": "10:17",
      "start": 617.466,
      "end": 619.8,
      "duration": 2.334,
      "text": "any immune rejection complications"
    },
    {
      "time": "10:19",
      "start": 619.8,
      "end": 621.5999999999999,
      "duration": 1.8,
      "text": "since the cells are their own."
    },
    {
      "time": "10:21",
      "start": 621.6,
      "end": 623.3340000000001,
      "duration": 1.734,
      "text": "So, there's still a ways to go here before"
    },
    {
      "time": "10:23",
      "start": 623.334,
      "end": 626.3489999999999,
      "duration": 3.015,
      "text": "this type of medicine\nis sort of mainstream,"
    },
    {
      "time": "10:26",
      "start": 626.349,
      "end": 628.066,
      "duration": 1.717,
      "text": "but, already, IPS cells have helped"
    },
    {
      "time": "10:28",
      "start": 628.066,
      "end": 630.566,
      "duration": 2.5,
      "text": "to create the precursors\nto a few different"
    },
    {
      "time": "10:30",
      "start": 630.566,
      "end": 634.8000000000001,
      "duration": 4.234,
      "text": "human organs in labs, such\nas the heart and the liver."
    },
    {
      "time": "10:34",
      "start": 634.8,
      "end": 636.233,
      "duration": 1.433,
      "text": "Now, before we finish up here,"
    },
    {
      "time": "10:36",
      "start": 636.233,
      "end": 637.5669999999999,
      "duration": 1.334,
      "text": "I just wanna answer two questions"
    },
    {
      "time": "10:37",
      "start": 637.567,
      "end": 639.633,
      "duration": 2.066,
      "text": "that might have come up for you."
    },
    {
      "time": "10:39",
      "start": 639.633,
      "end": 644.033,
      "duration": 4.4,
      "text": "So, one, what triggers our\nstem cells to differentiate?"
    },
    {
      "time": "10:44",
      "start": 644.033,
      "end": 646.533,
      "duration": 2.5,
      "text": "Well, it turns out that\nin normal situations,"
    },
    {
      "time": "10:46",
      "start": 646.533,
      "end": 648.333,
      "duration": 1.8,
      "text": "right, when the stem\ncell's just hangin' out,"
    },
    {
      "time": "10:48",
      "start": 648.333,
      "end": 650.8,
      "duration": 2.467,
      "text": "not doin' too much, it actually expresses"
    },
    {
      "time": "10:50",
      "start": 650.8,
      "end": 652.567,
      "duration": 1.767,
      "text": "a few different genes that helps"
    },
    {
      "time": "10:52",
      "start": 652.567,
      "end": 654.868,
      "duration": 2.301,
      "text": "to keep it undifferentiated."
    },
    {
      "time": "10:54",
      "start": 654.868,
      "end": 657.4670000000001,
      "duration": 2.599,
      "text": "So, there are a few proteins\nfloating around in the cell"
    },
    {
      "time": "10:57",
      "start": 657.467,
      "end": 660.367,
      "duration": 2.9,
      "text": "that prevents other genes\nfrom being activated"
    },
    {
      "time": "11:00",
      "start": 660.367,
      "end": 662.6329999999999,
      "duration": 2.266,
      "text": "and triggering differentiation."
    },
    {
      "time": "11:02",
      "start": 662.633,
      "end": 665.2330000000001,
      "duration": 2.6,
      "text": "But, when put in certain environments,"
    },
    {
      "time": "11:05",
      "start": 665.233,
      "end": 667.433,
      "duration": 2.2,
      "text": "this regulation can be overridden,"
    },
    {
      "time": "11:07",
      "start": 667.433,
      "end": 669.1659999999999,
      "duration": 1.733,
      "text": "and then, they can go on and differentiate"
    },
    {
      "time": "11:09",
      "start": 669.166,
      "end": 671.2,
      "duration": 2.034,
      "text": "into a more specialized cell."
    },
    {
      "time": "11:11",
      "start": 671.2,
      "end": 673.3330000000001,
      "duration": 2.133,
      "text": "The type of which depends on what specific"
    },
    {
      "time": "11:13",
      "start": 673.333,
      "end": 675.333,
      "duration": 2.0,
      "text": "little chemical signals are hanging around"
    },
    {
      "time": "11:15",
      "start": 675.333,
      "end": 677.4,
      "duration": 2.067,
      "text": "in the stem cell's environment."
    },
    {
      "time": "11:17",
      "start": 677.4,
      "end": 679.6329999999999,
      "duration": 2.233,
      "text": "So, for example, in the bone marrow,"
    },
    {
      "time": "11:19",
      "start": 679.633,
      "end": 682.133,
      "duration": 2.5,
      "text": "there are certain proteins\nthat hang around stem cells"
    },
    {
      "time": "11:22",
      "start": 682.133,
      "end": 683.933,
      "duration": 1.8,
      "text": "and induce some to differentiate"
    },
    {
      "time": "11:23",
      "start": 683.933,
      "end": 686.667,
      "duration": 2.734,
      "text": "into the specific blood cell types."
    },
    {
      "time": "11:26",
      "start": 686.667,
      "end": 689.166,
      "duration": 2.499,
      "text": "And finally, what's all this\nstuff you might have heard,"
    },
    {
      "time": "11:29",
      "start": 689.166,
      "end": 692.2,
      "duration": 3.034,
      "text": "maybe in the news, about cord blood?"
    },
    {
      "time": "11:32",
      "start": 692.2,
      "end": 694.533,
      "duration": 2.333,
      "text": "Well, from cord blood,\nwhich is blood taken"
    },
    {
      "time": "11:34",
      "start": 694.533,
      "end": 696.7330000000001,
      "duration": 2.2,
      "text": "from the placenta and the umbilical cord"
    },
    {
      "time": "11:36",
      "start": 696.733,
      "end": 699.266,
      "duration": 2.533,
      "text": "after the birth of a\nbaby, you can get lots"
    },
    {
      "time": "11:39",
      "start": 699.266,
      "end": 701.733,
      "duration": 2.467,
      "text": "of multipotent stem cells, and sometimes,"
    },
    {
      "time": "11:41",
      "start": 701.733,
      "end": 703.5659999999999,
      "duration": 1.833,
      "text": "some other stem cells that have been shown"
    },
    {
      "time": "11:43",
      "start": 703.566,
      "end": 705.2,
      "duration": 1.634,
      "text": "to be pluripotent."
    },
    {
      "time": "11:45",
      "start": 705.2,
      "end": 707.0,
      "duration": 1.8,
      "text": "So, this cord blood used\nto just be discarded"
    },
    {
      "time": "11:47",
      "start": 707.0,
      "end": 709.167,
      "duration": 2.167,
      "text": "after a baby's birth, but now,"
    },
    {
      "time": "11:49",
      "start": 709.167,
      "end": 710.933,
      "duration": 1.766,
      "text": "there's a lot of interest in keeping it"
    },
    {
      "time": "11:50",
      "start": 710.933,
      "end": 713.99,
      "duration": 3.057,
      "text": "because now we know it\ncontains all these stem cells."
    }
  ]
}